</bibRefCitation>
include the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Pixell, 1912" authorityName="Pixell" authorityYear="1912" box="[611,958,770,796]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protolaeospira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[611,787,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Protolaeospira</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pixell" box="[802,948,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Pixell, H. L. M. (1912) Polychaeta from the Pacific coast of North America. 1. Serpulidae, with a revised table of classification of the genus Spirorbis. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1912: 784 - 805." type="proceedings paper" year="1912">
Pixell, 
<number box="[886,948,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1912.0">1912</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, redefined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Knight-Jones" box="[1122,1351,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Knight-Jones, P. &amp; Walker, A. J. M. (1972) Spirorbinae (Serpulidae: Polychaeta) on limpets from the South Orkney Islands. Antarctic Survey Bulletin, 31, 33 - 40." type="journal article" year="1972">
Knight-Jones, 
<number box="[1292,1351,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<number box="[1407,1436,770,796]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="10.0">10</number>
species of the latter under the 
<emphasis box="[554,765,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Romanchellinae</emphasis>
. As defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Knight-Jones" box="[979,1438,809,835]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Knight-Jones, P. &amp; Walker, A. J. M. (1972) Spirorbinae (Serpulidae: Polychaeta) on limpets from the South Orkney Islands. Antarctic Survey Bulletin, 31, 33 - 40." type="journal article" year="1972">
Knight-Jones &amp; Walker (
<number box="[1309,1380,809,835]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1972.0">1972</number>
: 
<number box="[1394,1428,809,835]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="35.0">35</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName box="[151,329,848,873]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protolaeospira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,329,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Protolaeospira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the same as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bailey, 1969" authorityName="Bailey" authorityYear="1969" box="[511,830,848,874]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Marsipospira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,672,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Marsipospira</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bailey" box="[680,830,848,874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Bailey, J. H. (1969) Methods of brood protection as a basis for the reclassification of the Spirorbinae (Serpulidae), Journal of the Linnaean Society, Zoology, 48 (3), 387 - 403." type="journal article" year="1969">
Bailey, 
<number box="[771,830,848,874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and includes 
<taxonomicName authority="Pillai, 1970" authorityName="Pillai" authorityYear="1970" box="[996,1238,848,874]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pixellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[996,1088,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Pixellia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pillai" box="[1097,1238,848,874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" refString="Pillai, T. G. (1970) Studies on a collection of spirorbids from Ceylon, together with a critical and revision of spirorbid systematics, and an account of their phylogeny and zoogeography. Ceylon Journal of Science, Biological Sciences, 8 (2), 100 - 172." type="journal article" year="1970">
Pillai, 
<number box="[1175,1238,848,874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. P. Knight-Jones (
<number box="[160,226,886,912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1978.0">1978</number>
: 
<number box="[238,285,886,912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="233.0">233</number>
) describes the new species 
<taxonomicName box="[620,780,886,912]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Knightjonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="platyspira">
<emphasis box="[620,641,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[658,780,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">platyspira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is transferred to the new genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1260,1429,887,912]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Knightjonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1260,1429,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Knightjonesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName authority="P. Knight-Jones, 1978" authorityName="P. Knight-Jones" authorityYear="1978" box="[210,628,925,951]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Knightjonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="platyspira">
<emphasis box="[210,364,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">K. platyspira</emphasis>
P. Knight-Jones, 
<number box="[569,628,925,951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</taxonomicName>
as its 
<typeStatus box="[702,752,925,951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
species in the present paper.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1438,152,1376]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">
Based on the above and present studies, the differences among those genera may be summarized as follows. Opercular peduncle is winged in 
<taxonomicName box="[685,862,1002,1027]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Knightjonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[685,862,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Knightjonesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, wingless in 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1197,1002,1027]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Romanchella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1197,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Romanchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1215,1383,1002,1027]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Helicosiphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1215,1383,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Helicosiphon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,327,1041,1066]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protolaeospira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,327,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Protolaeospira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thoracic membranes of the two sides are not joined over the thorax in 
<taxonomicName box="[1173,1337,1041,1066]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Knightjonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1173,1337,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Knightjonesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as seen in Knight-Jones (
<number box="[363,429,1080,1106]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1978.0">1978</number>
: Fig. 
<number box="[499,528,1080,1106]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="18.0">18</number>
E) and 
<figureCitation box="[619,699,1080,1106]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A – D" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1739,1763]" captionTargetBox="[192,1378,462,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[175,1411,449,1730]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. A – D: Helicosiphon biscoensis figured from BM (NH) 1930.10.8.2984, Discovery Expedition, St. 175, South Shetlands, 200 m: A – C: Tubes showing uncoiling. Ontogenetically, however, the earliest formed part of the tube is coiled as shown in Figs. A and C. That part of the tube is missing in the specimen figured in B. Note also the angular sides of the earlier uncoiled parts of the tube. D, Worm, showing the straightened body, which conforms to that of spirorbids (see also description); the attachment stalk for the brood-pouch to the thorax can be seen dorsally (brood pouch missing). E, Knightjonesia platyspira (Knight-Jones) 1978 showing its winged peduncle, figured from among paratypes in BM (NH) 1969.492, Marion Island, Prince Edward Islands, collected by A. F. Villiers, 1973; see Fig. 2 for further details." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186794/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">
Figs. 
<number box="[688,699,1080,1106]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E &amp; 
<number box="[763,778,1080,1106]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="2.0">2</number>
E of the present paper, 
<taxonomicName authority="P. Knight-Jones" authorityName="P. Knight-Jones" box="[1073,1436,1080,1106]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Helicosiphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1073,1235,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Helicosiphon</emphasis>
P. Knight-Jones
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[160,224,1118,1144]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1978.0">1978</number>
: 
<number box="[235,340,1118,1144]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="232.5" valueMax="233.0" valueMin="232.0">232–233</number>
) and 
<figureCitation box="[406,489,1118,1144]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A – D" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1739,1763]" captionTargetBox="[192,1378,462,1703]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[175,1411,449,1730]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. A – D: Helicosiphon biscoensis figured from BM (NH) 1930.10.8.2984, Discovery Expedition, St. 175, South Shetlands, 200 m: A – C: Tubes showing uncoiling. Ontogenetically, however, the earliest formed part of the tube is coiled as shown in Figs. A and C. That part of the tube is missing in the specimen figured in B. Note also the angular sides of the earlier uncoiled parts of the tube. D, Worm, showing the straightened body, which conforms to that of spirorbids (see also description); the attachment stalk for the brood-pouch to the thorax can be seen dorsally (brood pouch missing). E, Knightjonesia platyspira (Knight-Jones) 1978 showing its winged peduncle, figured from among paratypes in BM (NH) 1969.492, Marion Island, Prince Edward Islands, collected by A. F. Villiers, 1973; see Fig. 2 for further details." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186794/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">
Fig 
<number box="[453,464,1118,1144]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
D
</figureCitation>
of the present paper, and in 
<taxonomicName box="[827,1004,1119,1144]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protolaeospira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[827,1004,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Protolaeospira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas it is joined over the thorax in 
<taxonomicName box="[182,340,1157,1182]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Romanchella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,340,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Romanchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Knight-Jones, 
<number box="[582,647,1157,1183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="1978.0">1978</number>
: 
<number box="[659,707,1157,1183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="229.0">229</number>
, Figs. 
<number box="[780,810,1157,1183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="16.0">16</number>
B &amp; 
<number box="[869,901,1157,1183]" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" value="17.0">17</number>
J). Collar chaetae do not consist of a fin and blade but simple blades in 
<taxonomicName box="[472,628,1196,1221]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Romanchella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[472,628,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Romanchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[644,802,1196,1221]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Helicosiphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[644,802,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Helicosiphon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[861,1027,1196,1221]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Knightjonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[861,1027,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Knightjonesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas they consist of a fin and blade in 
<taxonomicName box="[253,429,1235,1260]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protolaeospira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[253,429,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Protolaeospira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sickle-shaped chaetae (
<taxonomicName box="[723,840,1235,1260]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[723,840,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-chaetae) are absent in the thorax of 
<taxonomicName box="[1271,1436,1235,1260]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Knightjonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1436,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Knightjonesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[202,361,1273,1298]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Helicosiphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[202,361,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Helicosiphon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas they are present in 
<taxonomicName box="[714,871,1273,1298]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Romanchella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[714,871,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Romanchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1111,1273,1298]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protolaeospira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[931,1111,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Protolaeospira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The most anterior uncinal process is blunt and gouged in 
<taxonomicName box="[543,718,1312,1337]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Knightjonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[543,718,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Knightjonesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[734,897,1312,1337]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Romanchella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[734,897,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Romanchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1126,1312,1337]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Helicosiphon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[960,1126,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Helicosiphon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas it is bilobed in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,327,1351,1376]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Protolaeospira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="3" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,327,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="49">Protolaeospira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
